<h2 id="installing-bourbon">Installing Bourbon</h2>

<p>In Rails its a very simple to install. Switch to your selected project using your terminal install the Bourbon gem file.</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>$ gem bourbon
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>The run:</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>$ bundle install
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Restart your server. Then rename <code class="highlighter-rouge">application.css</code> to <code class="highlighter-rouge">application.scss</code> this SCSS extension allows us to use Sass:</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>mv app/assets/stylesheets/application.css app/assets/stylesheets/application.scss
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Delete the sprocket directive in application.scss:</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>*= require_tree .
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Import Bourbon at the beginning of <code class="highlighter-rouge">application.scss</code>. All additional stylesheets should get imported below Bourbon:</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>@import "bourbon";
@import 'neat';
@import 'base/base' # This is for bitters
</code></pre></div></div>

<hr />

<h2 id="conclusion">Conclusion</h2>
<p><a href="http://bourbon.io" target="_blank">Bourbon</a> gives you more than enough to create a great base for a siteŌĆÖs styling, and quickly too. But the best thing about <a href="http://bourbon.io" target="_blank">BourbonŌĆÖs</a> approach is that it also allows you to go a step further and provides the freedom you need to customise and add styles to it without becoming a pain to maintain.</p>

<p>Throw in the addition of <a href="http://neat.bourbon.io" target="_blank">Neat</a>, <a href="http://bitters.bourbon.io" target="_blank">Bitters</a> and <a href="http://refills.bourbon.io" target="_blank">Refills</a>, and you start to see why thoughtbotŌĆÖs <a href="http://bourbon.io" target="_blank">Bourbon</a> should seriously be in the running for your next project.</p>
